Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_1308
Response Text: I don't really have any complaints. I lived in Austin, then moved, then came back and since jumping back into the Cultural Arts Funding experience (in 2023) I have found that the team is very aware and active and working hard to make the program responsive to the needs of the artist and the community. And communities who are historically disenfranchised. So, that's a long way to say, I can't think of anything at the moment. I guess one thought is from other people, I know some legacy organizations have been upset about the people who serve on panels not being from Austin, and being unaware of the scene or their contributions, and about their funds getting cuts. So I know there is some balance that needs to be met between continuing to nurture important legacy orgs and also to support new and diverse arts organizations. This answer probably wasn't helpful... but that is my point of view at the moment.

